"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-coco-gauff-olympics-tennis-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Coco Gauff is the first U.S. tennis player to mathematically clinch a spot in the Olympic field, setting up for her Olympic debut in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Coco Gauff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\"}, {\"begin\": 133, \"end\": 138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999991966861714, \"rank\": 8.033144313859547e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gauff has accumulated enough points so that she is guaranteed to be among the top four U.S. women's singles players at the end of the 12-month Olympic qualifying window, which runs through the end of the French Open in early June.\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A nation can qualify no more than four singles players per gender.\", \"from\": 373, \"to\": 439, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The U.S. is expected to earn the full four spots for men and women.\", \"from\": 440, \"to\": 507, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Players can also qualify separately in doubles.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After Gauff, the highest-ranked American women in singles qualifying are Jessica Pegula, Emma Navarro and Madison Keys.\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 676, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9921041091110122, \"rank\": 0.007871809994954786, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 630, \"end\": 644, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Pegula\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Pegula\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Pegula\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Pegula\"}, {\"begin\": 646, \"end\": 658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Navarro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emma Navarro\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Navarro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Navarro\"}, {\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Keys\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madison Keys\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Keys\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Madison_Keys\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gauff made the Olympic team for Tokyo in 2021 at age 17, but announced five days before the Opening Ceremony that she had to withdraw after testing positive for COVID-19.\", \"from\": 678, \"to\": 848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9765727364542194, \"rank\": 0.023987898072152646, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 786, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Paralympics\", \"score\": 0.999664745049225, \"rank\": 0.00032230856864609754, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Paralympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Paralympics\"}, {\"begin\": 839, \"end\": 847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9996181894384116, \"rank\": 0.0003562006596992611, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She would have been the youngest Olympic tennis player since 2000 - when Croatia's Mario Ancic competed at 16 years old - according to the OlyMADMen.\", \"from\": 850, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 923, \"end\": 930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\", \"score\": 0.9557313669353492, \"rank\": 0.046303170601715814, \"text\": \"Croatia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Croatia_men's_national_handball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 933, \"end\": 944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mario_An\\u010di\\u0107\", \"score\": 0.9999998494743181, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mario Ancic\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mario_An\\u010di\\u0107\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mario_An\\u010di\\u0107\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gauff won her first Grand Slam singles title at the U.S. Open in September and is ranked third in the world.\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In January, Gauff said that, ideally, she wants to play singles, doubles and mixed doubles at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympic tennis will be at Roland Garros, where Gauff was runner-up at the 2022 French Open in singles and doubles.\", \"from\": 1223, \"to\": 1337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One of the goals I wrote down on my vision thing, vision note, in my phone, was to win a medal in the Olympics,\\\" she said in January.\", \"from\": 1339, \"to\": 1473, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will be completely honest, I do not really care what event it is in.\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like a gold, silver or bronze, whatever medal it is, is one of those things it does not matter.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1648, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, it does matter.\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1670, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Obviously I want to win in singles.\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I feel like I would appreciate it just as much whether it was in singles or doubles.\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1791, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's not the same to me as a Slam, I guess, in a way.\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 1845, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"score\": 0.9999999965557436, \"rank\": 3.444195622698978e-09, \"text\": \"Slam\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Grand_Slam_of_Curling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I just put 'I want a medal at any of the events.'\\\"\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Division ofNBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1900, \"end\": 1910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"score\": 0.9999836047950589, \"rank\": 1.639547360374597e-05, \"text\": \"A Division\", \"types\": [\"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Scottish_Football_League\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"DISCLAIMER: This site and the products offered are for entertainment purposes only, and there is no gambling offe